  <description type="morphology">Heads 10–100+; bracts linear-oblanceolate to narrowly oblanceolate, (4–)15–90 × 2–9 mm. Involucres 2.4–3.8 × 3.7–8.7 mm. Phyllaries linear to linear-attenuate or subulate, subequal, membranous margins 0.5–1 mm wide, apices acute; outer 1.7–2.8 × 0.4–0.6(–0.9) mm; inner 2.2–3.9 × 0.3–0.7(–1) mm. Cypselae obovoid, sometimes wingless; pappus awns (0–)0.4–1.2 mm, to 2/3 length of cypselae. 2n = 36.</description>
